FBIS3-29508 "dreas034_a_94023" FBIS-EAS-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 February 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Food Makers Use Imported Rice OW1802123694 Tokyo KYODO in English 1135 GMT 18 Feb 94 OW1802123694 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Feb. 18 KYODO -- Japanese food manufacturer Ajinomoto Co. on Friday [18 February] announced a decision to use imported rice in its frozen foods such as pilaff. Sushi chain operator Kyotaru Co. also said it is experimenting with imported rice for use in its takeout and restaurant food. Nichiro Corp. said it will start selling frozen pilaff based on Thai rice next month. Nippon Suisan Kaisha Ltd. also plans to use imported rice in its frozen food.
